{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 14:57:06.556809", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"dhcp_server\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"dhcp_missing_subnet\"]\n\nReasoning (concise):\n- Hosts in 10.2.1.0/24 have L2 connectivity but no IPv4 addresses.\n- Distribution router for that subnet (10.2.1.1) is up and can reach DHCP server.\n- DHCP server configuration lacks a subnet declaration for 10.2.1.0/24, so it will not issue leases for that network.\n- Therefore, DHCP server configuration omission (missing subnet) is the root cause.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2541, "output_tokens": 137, "total_tokens": 2678, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
